<manpage>
    <sample url="sdk\operating_system\crt\libc\stdio\perror">perror</sample>
    <title>perror</title>
    <volume>C 运行库函数</volume>
    <routine_idx> stio_idx.htm </routine_idx>

    <description>
        <para>打印错误信息。</para>
    </description>

    <syntax>
        <return_val>void</return_val>
        <func_name>perror</func_name>
        <parameters>
            <func_param>
                <param_type>const char*</param_type>
                <param_name>string</param_name>
                <param_note>
                    <para>指向错误信息字符串的指针</para>
                </param_note>
            </func_param>
        </parameters>
    </syntax>

    <return>
        <NoReturnValue/>
    </return>

    <remarks>
        <para>perror函数是打印一个错误信息，string首先被打印，紧跟着是冒号“：”然后是系统错误信息，它由最后库调用产生的，最后是一个换行符。如果string是空指针或指向空串，perror 仅打印系统错误信息。</para>
    </remarks>

    <requirements>
        <routine>
            <routine_name>perror</routine_name>
            <headerfile>stdio.h</headerfile>
            <compatibility>ANSI, Windows 2000, Elastos </compatibility>
        </routine>
    </requirements>

    <example>
<pre>
//==========================================================================
// Copyright (c) 2000-2004,  Elastos, Inc.  All Rights Reserved.
//==========================================================================

/* perror.cpp: This program attempts to open a file which doesn&apos;t exist,
 * then attempts to use sqrt to calculates the square root of a negative.
 */

#include &lt;stdio.h&gt;
#include &lt;math.h&gt;

int main()
{
    FILE *fp;  //file pointer
    double x = -10;
    double y;
    //f:\file.txt doesn&apos;t exist.
    fp = fopen(&quot;U:\\file.txt&quot;, &quot;w&quot;);
    if (fp == NULL) {
        perror(&quot;perror says open the file failed&quot;);
    }
    else {
        perror(&quot;perror says open file no error&quot;);
        fclose(fp);
    }
    //the sqrt&apos;s argument is minor to zero
    y = sqrt(x);
    perror(&quot;The argument of the funtion is out of domian&quot;);

    return 0;
}
</pre>
    </example>
<result>
perror says open the file failed:No such file of directory
The argument of the function is out of domian:Domain error
</result>

    

